def: An albuminous substance existing in the blood, and in otheranimal fluids, which either alone or with fibrinoplastin orparaglobulin forms fibrin, and thus causes coagulation.
A fine wide wooled fabric much used for women's dresses.
Of or pertaining to physiology; relating to the science of thefunctions of living organism; as, physiological botany or chemistry.
To acquire desert; to gain value; to receive benefit; toprofit. [Obs.] Beau. & Fl.
Of or pertaining to Paraguay.-- n.

A fitting out, or equipment, as of a ship for a voyage, or of aperson for an expedition in an unoccupied region or residence in aforeign land; things required for equipment; the expense of, orallowance made for, equipment, as by the government of the UnitedStates to a diplomatic agent going abroad.
The act of developing a new coat of hair, a new set offeathers, scales, etc.; -- opposed to ecdysis.
One who maintains or attends a ferry.
See Spoom. [Obs.]We might have spooned before the wind as well as they. Pepys.
